President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Jonathan Lippman to be a member of the Board of Directors of the State Justice Institute. Lippman is currently the Chief Judge of the State of New York and Chief Judge of the New York Court of Appeals. He has spent his entire legal career in the New York State court system and has held various roles within it. Lippman is also a member of the Board of Directors of the Conference of Chief Justices and has received numerous awards for his judicial excellence.

President Obama has also announced his intent to appoint John F. Sopko as the Special Inspector General for Afghanistan Reconstruction. Sopko is currently a partner at Akin Gump Strauss Hauer & Feld LLP and has previously served in various positions within the U.S. government, including as Chief Counsel for Oversight and Investigations for the U.S. House Committee on Energy and Commerce. He has also held roles at the U.S. Department of Commerce and the U.S. Department of Justice. Sopko holds a B.A. in Economics and Sociology from the University of Pennsylvania and a J.D. from Case Western Reserve University School of Law.